<h3>Web References</h3>

<p>Many of the techniques I learned for CSS, HTML, JavaScript, and PHP are from the <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/">W3 Schools</a> site. This site is a long standing, free (advertising-supported) reference for web developers of all levels of experience.</p>

<p>This page is laid out using CSS to change width with the user's screen size. This specific technique, as well as precise min/max pixel values that will provide visually pleasing widths for most resolutions, were created by <a href="http://chriscoyier.net/">Chris Coyier</a>, and may be found at his <a href="http://css-tricks.com/the-perfect-fluid-width-layout/">CSS-tricks.com</a>.</p>

<p>To utilize a PHP file as a CSS style sheet, and thus be able to define constants for colors and other repetitive elements, certain headers are required. The method I used to do this was created by <a href="http://icant.co.uk/">Christian Heilmann</a>, and can be found at <a href="http://icant.co.uk/articles/cssconstants/">icant.co.uk - everything Christian Heilmann</a>.</p>

<p>Examples of how to embed font files in CSS code (Gentium, in particular) is by <a href="http://shelleypowers.burningbird.net/about">Shelley Powers</a>, found at <a href="http://realtech.burningbird.net/graphics/css/embedded-fonts-font-face">Burningbird RealTech</a></p>

<p>How to show and hide block elements through JavaScript was demonstrated by <a href="http://arvind2111.com/">Arvind Satyanarayan </a>, found at <a href="http://blog.movalog.com/a/javascript-toggle-visibility/">Movalog</a>, as well as at <a href="http://www.w3schools.com/CSS/pr_class_display.asp">w3Schools</a>.</p>

